		<RECORD id="0-0-0-29908" number="34464" version="2030">
			<HEADING>Chapter 39: Engine Idling</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-3991" name="T15C039"/>Chapter 39: Engine Idling</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
			<RECORD id="0-0-0-29909" number="34465" version="2030">
				<PARA>
					<PARAFORMAT justify="center">(Title amended City Record 7/15/2021, eff. 8/14/2021) [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
					</PARAFORMAT>
				</PARA>
			</RECORD>
		</LEVEL>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129572" number="34466" version="2030">
								<HEADING>§ 39-01 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-3993" name="T15C039_39-01"/>§ 39-01 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions.</CHARFORMAT>
								</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-29910" number="34467" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Legally authorized emergency motor vehicle.</CHARFORMAT> For purposes of § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="24-163" destination-id="0-0-0-0">24-163</LINK> of the Administrative Code, the term &quot;legally authorized emergency motor vehicle&quot; shall mean: [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129575" number="34468" version="2030">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>a motor vehicle that is an authorized emergency vehicle as defined by § 101 of the Vehicle and Traffic Law; or [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129576" number="34469" version="2030">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any bus being operated as a cooling center by, or pursuant to a contract with, the city of New York. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-064]<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">
											</CHARFORMAT>
										</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129573" number="34470" version="2244">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Marginal Street.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Marginal street&quot; shall have the meaning set forth in 34 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T34C004_4-01" destination-id="0-0-0-8415">4-01</LINK>.</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-133764" number="34471" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Processing Device.</CHARFORMAT> For purposes of § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="24-163" destination-id="0-0-0-0">24-163</LINK> of the Administrative Code, the term &quot;processing device&quot; shall mean: [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-074]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-133767" number="34472" version="2363">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>a device that accomplishes the function for which the vehicle or equipment was designed, other than transporting goods or people, via a mechanical connection to the engine, including but not limited to operating a lift, crane, pump, drill, hoist, or mixer; or [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-082]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-133766" number="34473" version="2244">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>a system that controls the environment of temperature-sensitive cargo or substances, including but not limited to food, provided that such cargo or substances are being transported in a vehicle designed for the transportation of such cargo or substances. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-074]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-133765" number="34474" version="2502">
									<PARA>The term &quot;processing device&quot; shall not include a heater or air conditioner operated for cabin comfort. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-074]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-29911" number="34475" version="1817">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Street.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Street&quot; shall have the meaning set forth in subdivision 13 of § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1-112" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1-112</LINK> of the Administrative Code of the City of New York, except that for the purposes of this rule &quot;street&quot; shall include &quot;marginal streets&quot;.</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-29912" number="34476" version="2363">
									<PARA>(Amended City Record 7/15/2021, eff. 8/14/2021; amended City Record 5/23/2022, eff. 6/22/2022; amended City Record 1/18/2023, eff. 2/17/2023) [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-082]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129574" number="34477" version="2772">
								<HEADING>§ 39-02 Adjacent to Any Public or Non-Public School or Any Park Under the Jurisdiction of the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-3995" name="T15C039_39-02"/>§ 39-02 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Adjacent to Any Public or Non-Public School or Any Park Under the Jurisdiction of the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation.</CHARFORMAT>
								</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-29913" number="34478" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Adjacent.</CHARFORMAT> A motor vehicle is adjacent to any public or non-public school or any park under the jurisdiction of the New York city department of parks and recreation when such vehicle is parked, stopped, or standing within a lane of traffic on a block face on which a school or park is located, unless the vehicle is separated from the school or park by a median. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147709" number="34479" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A lane of traffic includes traffic lanes, bus lanes, all forms of bike lanes, turning bays, parking areas, and shoulders. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147708" number="34480" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A block face consists of both sides of a city street between two intersections. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147707" number="34481" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Where one street meets another without crossing it, dividing one side of the street into two blocks but not dividing the opposite side (forming a T shape), the side that is not divided by the intersecting street is deemed to be divided into two corresponding block faces as if the intersecting street extended to the other side. However, where a school or park is located on the side of the street that is not divided by the intersecting street, the side that is not divided by the intersecting street is divided into two corresponding block faces as if the curb furthest from the school or park extends to the other side of the street. The below example illustrates this definition. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147706" number="34482" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(4)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A median is a raised area that separates lanes of traffic. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147705" number="34483" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Example.</CHARFORMAT> [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147703" number="34484" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<PICTURE id="0-0-0-19240-img" object-class="folio objects" name="15RCNY39-02.jpg" href="#!-- #EXECUTIVE:HOME_PATH --#/img/15RCNY39-02.jpg" width="10080" height="9156" left-border-line-color="0" left-border-line-width="0" left-border-space="0" right-border-line-color="0" right-border-line-width="0" right-border-space="0" top-border-line-color="0" top-border-line-width="0" top-border-space="0" bottom-border-line-color="0" bottom-border-line-width="0" bottom-border-space="0"/>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147704" number="34485" version="2772">
									<PARA>In the diagram above, the numbered vehicles are: [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147702" number="34486" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>1 - ADJACENT to SP1 because it is parked on the same side of the line running from the opposite curb furthest from SP1. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147701" number="34487" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>2 - ADJACENT to SP2 and SP3 as it is parked on the same block face. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147700" number="34488" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>3 - ADJACENT to SP1 as it is parked on the same block face. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147699" number="34489" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>4 - NOT ADJACENT as it is parked on a block face with no school/park. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147698" number="34490" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>5 - NOT ADJACENT as it is parked on a block face that is separated from SP3 by a raised median. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147697" number="34491" version="2772">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>6 - ADJACENT to SP2 and SP3 as it is parked on the same block face. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-147696" number="34492" version="2772">
									<PARA>Curbs where parked vehicles would be adjacent are in BOLD. [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-29914" number="34493" version="2772">
									<PARA>(Amended City Record 8/27/2024, eff. 9/26/2024) [<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">ALP S-101]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
